    "Using a breadth-first search strategy, they determined the optimal sequence for adding a molecule's nodes and edges in the training data.",
    "The molecular graph generation process was then broken down into parallelizable one-step graph modification procedures.",
    "In the generation phase, GraphAF generates a molecule by sampling it repeatedly, a technique that permits the use of chemical domain knowledge in valency testing.",
    "Even without chemical knowledge criteria, GraphAF achieved a 68% validity rate on the ZINC data set, which increased to 100% with chemical rules.",
    "One significant drawback of flow-based models is the time needed to complete the intricate hyperparameter tuning."
